&lt;br&gt;

&gt; What should you do when you want to customize your beans? As usual, extend WebMvcConfigurerAdapter (annotate the new class with @Component) and do your customizations.&lt;br&gt;
&gt; So, bottom line of the particular problem: Don’t use @EnableWebMvc in
&gt; Spring Boot, just include spring-web as a maven/gradle dependency and
&gt; it will be autoconfigured.&lt;br&gt;

